  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Part of #1586, our logic in our propose block RPC call is as follows:\r\n```go\r\nstate, err := ReceiveBlock(block)\r\nif err != nil {\r\n    return err\r\n}\r\nif err := UpdateChainHead(block, state); err != nil {\r\n    return err\r\n}\r\n```\r\nour logic in regular sync is as follows:\r\n```go\r\nstate, err := ReceiveBlock(block)\r\nif err != nil {\r\n    log.Error(err)\r\n}\r\nif err := UpdateChainHead(block, state); err != nil {\r\n   log.Error(err)\r\n}\r\n```\r\nWe should not update the chain head in regular sync if the received block fails processing, as this led to inconsistencies in states between nodes.",
